remarks:
Define the range of a class.  For example, ` F = { <. 2 , 6 >. , <. 3 , 9 >. } -> ran F = { 6 , 9 } ` ( ~ ex-rn ). Contrast with domain (defined in ~ df-dm ).  For alternate definitions, see ~ dfrn2 , ~ dfrn3 , and ~ dfrn4 .  The notation " ` ran ` " is used by Enderton; other authors sometimes use script R or script W. (Contributed by NM, 1-Aug-1994.)
